{
  "page": "War for the Stepstones",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"margin: 4px 10%; border: 1px solid #aaa; background:#fbfbfb;\"><tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"padding: 2px 0 2px 0.5em;border-left: 10px solid #1e90ff;\">\n<div style=\"width: 50px;\"><img alt=\"Mbox notice.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/40px-Mbox_notice.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/60px-Mbox_notice.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/Mbox_notice.png/80px-Mbox_notice.png 2x\" />\n</div></td><td style=\"border: none; padding: 0.25em 0.9em; width: 100%;\"> <b>Note:</b> The title of this article is conjecture and may be subject to change.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background: #B0C4DE; text-align:center;\">War for the Stepstones</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Craghas_Crabfeeder_and_Daemon_Targaryen_by_Douglas_Wheatley_(Fire_%26_Blood).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Craghas Crabfeeder and Daemon Targaryen by Douglas Wheatley (Fire &amp; Blood).jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7f/Craghas_Crabfeeder_and_Daemon_Targaryen_by_Douglas_Wheatley_%28Fire_%26_Blood%29.jpg/350px-Craghas_Crabfeeder_and_Daemon_Targaryen_by_Douglas_Wheatley_%28Fire_%26_Blood%29.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"271\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7f/Craghas_Crabfeeder_and_Daemon_Targaryen_by_Douglas_Wheatley_%28Fire_%26_Blood%29.jpg/525px-Craghas_Crabfeeder_and_Daemon_Targaryen_by_Douglas_Wheatley_%28Fire_%26_Blood%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/7/7f/Craghas_Crabfeeder_and_Daemon_Targaryen_by_Douglas_Wheatley_%28Fire_%26_Blood%29.jpg 2x\" /></a><div><div style=\"width:100%; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;\">Daemon Targaryen slays Craghas Crabfeeder in the War for the Stepstones by Douglas Wheatley for <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i></div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Date</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/106_AC\" title=\"106 AC\">106</a>–<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_115_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">115&#160;AC</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Place</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Result</th><td>\nDaemon forms his kingdom and later abandons it</td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<table style=\"width:100%; text-align:left;\">\n<tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Combatants</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/20px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/30px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/40px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Daemon's sellsword army<br />\n<hr />\n<b><a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Stepstones_and_the_Narrow_Sea\" title=\"King of the Stepstones and the Narrow Sea\">Kingdom of the Stepstones and the Narrow Sea</a></b></td>\n    <td width=\"50%\"><a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\"><img alt=\"Myr.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f1/Myr.svg/16px-Myr.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f1/Myr.svg/24px-Myr.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f1/Myr.svg/32px-Myr.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\"><img alt=\"Lys.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/16px-Lys.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/24px-Lys.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fd/Lys.svg/32px-Lys.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\"><img alt=\"Tyrosh.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/16px-Tyrosh.svg.png\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/24px-Tyrosh.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/32px-Tyrosh.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a></b><br /><a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\"><img alt=\"House Martell.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/60/House_Martell.svg/20px-House_Martell.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/60/House_Martell.svg/30px-House_Martell.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/60/House_Martell.svg/40px-House_Martell.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Principality of <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Commanders</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\"><img alt=\"House Targaryen.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/20px-House_Targaryen.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/30px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1e/House_Targaryen.svg/40px-House_Targaryen.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Stepstones_and_the_Narrow_Sea\" title=\"King of the Stepstones and the Narrow Sea\">King of the Stepstones and the Narrow Sea</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\"><img alt=\"House Velaryon.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/20px-House_Velaryon.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"22\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/30px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/5f/House_Velaryon.svg/40px-House_Velaryon.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a><br />\n<hr />\nKings of the Narrow Sea</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\"><img alt=\"Myr.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/f1/Myr.svg/20px-Myr.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f1/Myr.svg/30px-Myr.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f1/Myr.svg/40px-Myr.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Prince-admiral <a href=\"/index.php/Craghas_Drahar\" title=\"Craghas Drahar\">Craghas Drahar</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\"><img alt=\"Tyrosh.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/20px-Tyrosh.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/30px-Tyrosh.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d7/Tyrosh.svg/40px-Tyrosh.svg.png 2x\" /></a> Captain-general <a href=\"/index.php/Racallio_Ryndoon\" title=\"Racallio Ryndoon\">Racallio Ryndoon</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/House_Martell\" title=\"House Martell\"><img alt=\"House Martell.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/60/House_Martell.svg/20px-House_Martell.svg.png\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/60/House_Martell.svg/30px-House_Martell.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/6/60/House_Martell.svg/40px-House_Martell.svg.png 2x\" /></a> <a href=\"/index.php/Qoren_Martell\" title=\"Qoren Martell\">Qoren Martell</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Dorne\" title=\"Prince of Dorne\">Prince of Dorne</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Strength</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a><br />Fleet of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a><br />Army of sellswords and adventurers</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      Garrison and fleet of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dornish allies</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color: #B0C4DE; text-align: center;\"><b>Casualties</b></td></tr><tr><td width=\"50%\" style=\"border-right:1px dotted #aaa;\">Unknown</td>\n    <td width=\"50%\">                                      <a href=\"/index.php/Craghas_Drahar\" title=\"Craghas Drahar\">Craghas Drahar</a>†</td></tr>\n</tbody></table></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>war for the Stepstones</b> occurred when Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_the_Tides\" title=\"Lord of the Tides\">Lord of the Tides</a>, fought a series of land and naval battles with the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a> for control of the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a>, islands between the <a href=\"/index.php/Broken_Arm\" title=\"Broken Arm\">Broken Arm</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Disputed_Lands\" title=\"Disputed Lands\">Disputed Lands</a> in the southern <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Events\">Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=War_for_the_Stepstones&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>After defeating <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_96_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">96&#160;AC</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a> invaded the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a> to subdue outlaws and <a href=\"/index.php/Pirates\" title=\"Pirates\">pirates</a> living in the islands. While the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> were appreciative at first, they came to resent the high tolls imposed by the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> on trade in the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>. Foremost among the aggrieved <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westerosi</a> was the Sea Snake, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After his older brother, King <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I Targaryen</a>, refused to name him heir, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> decided to establish his own kingdom. Daemon joined forces with Corlys in trying to wrestle control of the Stepstones from the so-called Three Daughters. While Corlys commanded the <a href=\"/index.php/Velaryon_fleet\" title=\"Velaryon fleet\">Velaryon fleet</a>, Daemon led an army of <a href=\"/index.php/Sellsword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellsword\">sellswords</a>, cutthroats, landless adventurers, and second sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/106_AC\" title=\"106 AC\">106&#160;AC</a>, Daemon invaded the Stepstones atop his dragon, <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a>. Despite inferior numbers, they inflicted a string of defeats on the Triarchy for two years before Daemon slew <a href=\"/index.php/Craghas_Drahar\" title=\"Craghas Drahar\">Craghas Drahar</a> of Myr in single combat with his blade, <a href=\"/index.php/Dark_Sister\" title=\"Dark Sister\">Dark Sister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Viserys supported Daemon's campaign with <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>. By <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_109_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">109&#160;AC</a>, Daemon's armies controlled all but two of the Stepstones, and the Sea Snake's fleets had naval supremacy. Daemon chose the title <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Stepstones_and_the_Narrow_Sea\" title=\"King of the Stepstones and the Narrow Sea\">King of the Stepstones and the Narrow Sea</a> and received his crown from Corlys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_110_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">110&#160;AC</a>, however, the Triarchy dispatched a counterattack led by <a href=\"/index.php/Racallio_Ryndoon\" title=\"Racallio Ryndoon\">Racallio Ryndoon</a>, supported by newly-acquired <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dornish</a> allies. Fighting continued in <a href=\"/index.php/111_AC\" title=\"111 AC\">111&#160;AC</a>, when King Daemon withdrew to court at <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> for six months. Daemon struggled to defend the Stepstones against the Triarchy and their allies from Dorne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Upon hearing of the death of his estranged wife, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Rhea_Royce\" title=\"Rhea Royce\">Rhea Royce</a>, in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_115_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">115&#160;AC</a>, Daemon left his seat at <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodstone\" title=\"Bloodstone\">Bloodstone</a> in the Stepstones and attempted to claim <a href=\"/index.php/Runestone\" title=\"Runestone\">Runestone</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>. Although he failed to acquire Rhea's inheritance, Daemon then married Corlys's daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Laena_Velaryon\" title=\"Laena Velaryon\">Laena Velaryon</a>, and abandoned the Stepstones altogether. Five other men, including Racallio,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_the_hooded_hand.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> followed Daemon as Kings of the Narrow Sea before the Triarchy and Dornish alliance ended the sellsword kingdom he had created in the <a href=\"/index.php/Daughters%27_War\" title=\"Daughters&#39; War\">Daughters' War</a> of 131-134 AC.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=War_for_the_Stepstones&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Let <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon</a> play at war. It keeps him out of trouble.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys I Targaryen\">Viserys I Targaryen</a> to his court</cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>In the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a>, my enemies learned to run and hide when they saw <a href=\"/index.php/Caraxes\" title=\"Caraxes\">Caraxes</a>'s wings or heard his roar ... but they had no <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> of their own.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_blacks_and_the_greens.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=War_for_the_Stepstones&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_re